<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4738751>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 22–27. Male palp (22–24) and bulb (25–27) of Poecilochroa hamipalpis. 22, 26 ventral; 23, 27 retrolateral; 24 dorsal; 25 prolateral. Scale bars: 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Cn—conductor, Db—dorsal branch of tibial apophysis, Eb—base of the embolus, Pb—projection on the base of the embolus, Pf—prolateral fold of the conductor, Sd—sperm duct, Vb—ventral branch of tibial apophysis." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4738751/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4738767>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 65–66. Distribution records of studied species in Tajikistan. Drassodex tajikistanicus sp. n.—diamond; Nomisia palaestina—triangle; Poecilochroa hamipalpis—circle; Z. khatlonicus sp. n.—star; Zelotes anatolyi sp. n.—square. One single symbol may refer to more than one closely located records. Frame on Fig. 66 refers to Fig. 65." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4738767/files/figure.png" .

